column5: Spent 3 hrs on bass for the first time in a month, yep there are some hawgs to be caught still!
A really nice one Rich. Topwater?

Thanks sir, nope it was the dead slow spinnerbait death roll that was annihilating them. Couldn't rise a fish on topwater. Though I can't figure out why as they were indeed surfacing like crazy that evening.

Thanks sir, nope it was the dead slow spinnerbait death roll that was annihilating them. Couldn't rise a fish on topwater. Though I can't figure out why as they were indeed surfacing like crazy that evening.  Probably chasing shad.  Next time break out some spoons and try vertical jigging, it can be absolutely insane when you stumble onto a big school    Nice fish man!
Good one.. action angling strikes again!
That's a nice looking bucket. Sometimes the big ones get pretty nasty looking, but that one still has all its fins lol!  Nice fish.
That is an impressive fish!  Almost looks like you caught it from shore in someones backyard. lol
Well I did catch it from shore but I was on the public side of the fence, lol  Thanks everyone!! Now I'm officially done with largies for the season, bring on the esox and salmonoids!
Nice bas Rich, man o man nothing better than seeing 1 or 2 of those every time you head out
Beady-eyed beauty. When it comes to bass, I definitly have a soft spot for largies! Good job, hope there's more for you before the season ends.
